WEBVTT

00:07.462 --> 00:09.147
WOMAN: We need
to turn around.

00:09.149 --> 00:10.965
We're nowhere
near Park Avenue.

00:10.967 --> 00:12.650
You saying I
can't read a map?

00:12.652 --> 00:14.185
Or street signs.
Give me that.

00:14.187 --> 00:15.820
MAN: Okay, look,
you already ate half of it.

00:15.822 --> 00:17.605
I didn't eat half of it.
You ate half.

00:17.607 --> 00:19.857
This is not half of it.
So, maybe I should only give you

00:19.859 --> 00:21.476
half of your money...
Half of it... Oh! Come on!

00:21.478 --> 00:23.278
So, I got us
on the list at the club,

00:23.280 --> 00:24.412
and don't you dare wear red,

00:24.414 --> 00:26.164
because I just bought
the perfect red dress.

00:26.166 --> 00:28.533
MAN 2: ...tickets!
Who wants tickets?

00:28.535 --> 00:30.034
Free comedy show!

00:30.569 --> 00:32.787
(people screaming)

00:35.874 --> 00:37.875
GORMLEY:
<i>You're kidding me.</i>

00:37.877 --> 00:38.993
<i>In Times Square? All right.</i>

00:38.995 --> 00:39.994
(hangs up phone)

00:39.996 --> 00:43.298
Reagan, Baez,
we got a fresh one.

00:43.300 --> 00:45.767
Hello?

00:47.469 --> 00:49.587
Hello?!

00:57.112 --> 01:00.198
ALL:
Surprise!

01:00.200 --> 01:02.033
(all cheering, Gormley laughs)

01:02.035 --> 01:03.534
(horn sounding)
(laughs)

01:03.536 --> 01:05.737
What do you think, Sarge?
Baked it myself.

01:05.739 --> 01:06.537
Really?

01:06.539 --> 01:07.905
That's right.
No.

01:07.907 --> 01:09.958
He was just the only guy willing
to cough up two bucks for it.

01:09.960 --> 01:11.192
Mm. Yeah, right.

01:11.194 --> 01:12.577
Well, I got
a present

01:12.579 --> 01:13.711
for the two of you.

01:13.713 --> 01:14.912
Shooting on 43rd
and Times Square.

01:14.914 --> 01:17.081
So, grab your coats
and get a move on.

01:17.083 --> 01:18.249
What? Come on, Sarge.

01:18.251 --> 01:19.550
You got to make a wish first.

01:21.203 --> 01:22.920
All right! All right!
Yay!

01:22.922 --> 01:24.088
(applause)
Didn't come true.

01:24.090 --> 01:25.206
You're still here.

01:25.208 --> 01:26.540
(laughs)
Let's go.

01:26.542 --> 01:28.009
Back to work.
Ah.

01:31.764 --> 01:34.265
MAN: And that's why
I'm so proud to be here

01:34.267 --> 01:36.401
on the flight deck
of the USS <i>Intrepid.</i>

01:36.403 --> 01:39.487
You know, first question
I always get is,

01:39.489 --> 01:41.656
"Pete, what's it like
up in space?"

01:41.658 --> 01:43.441
And the truth is,
I don't think

01:43.443 --> 01:46.194
the words have been
invented yet to describe it.

01:46.196 --> 01:50.865
Just how black that sky is,
just how bright those stars are.

01:50.867 --> 01:53.201
And of course,
the second question that people

01:53.203 --> 01:54.619
always ask me is,

01:54.621 --> 01:57.288
"How the hell do you go
to the bathroom up there?"

01:57.290 --> 02:00.741
(laughter)

02:02.594 --> 02:05.079
Well, all you really
need to know

02:05.081 --> 02:08.098
is that I was sure glad
it worked back in '99

02:08.101 --> 02:09.967
when I was coming back

02:09.969 --> 02:11.686
to Earth in <i>Discovery.</i>

02:11.688 --> 02:13.388
Two of the hydraulic systems

02:13.390 --> 02:14.689
had already failed.

02:14.691 --> 02:16.590
One of 'em was looking
pretty iffy.

02:16.592 --> 02:18.109
I'm trying to bring this bird

02:18.111 --> 02:20.144
back down on a lakebed,

02:20.146 --> 02:24.065
with all the alarms going off
around me in the cockpit...

02:24.067 --> 02:26.984
Got to tell you,
if I was gonna murder somebody,

02:26.986 --> 02:28.986
I'd definitely pick
a more secluded location.

02:28.988 --> 02:30.705
Shooter either
has a lot of balls,

02:30.707 --> 02:31.956
or not a lot of brains.

02:31.958 --> 02:35.443
Careful. I made a whole career
off of that combination.

02:35.445 --> 02:37.462
MAN: Here's the vic's
cell phone, Detective.

02:37.464 --> 02:38.713
What do you got?

02:38.715 --> 02:40.715
Martin Cahill, 28 years old.

02:40.717 --> 02:43.167
Address says he lives uptown.

02:43.169 --> 02:46.554
Rorsch Financial I.D.
says he works downtown.

02:46.556 --> 02:48.840
Looks like he died
texting somebody named Tess.

02:48.842 --> 02:50.641
"Heading home now. XOXO."

02:50.643 --> 02:52.143
But he never pressed send.

02:52.145 --> 02:53.678
Great.
That means it'll be us

02:53.680 --> 02:55.897
walking through
Tess's door instead.

02:55.899 --> 02:57.348
Yeah, worst part of the job.

02:57.350 --> 02:58.516
Tell me about it.

02:58.518 --> 02:59.901
We got witnesses.

02:59.903 --> 03:02.403
Okay, who saw what over here?

03:02.405 --> 03:04.272
Oh, I saw the whole thing.

03:04.274 --> 03:08.309
Guy came out of the crowd,
shot the other guy, walked off.

03:08.311 --> 03:09.527
Nothing said?
No argument?

03:09.529 --> 03:10.828
MAN:
Nah, this guy--

03:10.830 --> 03:12.530
he's calm, you know,
like a cucumber.

03:12.532 --> 03:13.831
BAEZ:
Cool...

03:13.833 --> 03:15.833
as a cucumber,
but we get your drift.

03:15.835 --> 03:17.919
Okay, look--
what'd the guy look like?

03:17.921 --> 03:20.505
Oh, he was a tall white guy
in a parka.

03:20.507 --> 03:22.323
Uh-huh.
Ah! No, no!

03:22.325 --> 03:24.158
He is short guy
with baseball cap, okay?

03:24.160 --> 03:25.659
And he's black.
WOMAN: He was white.

03:25.661 --> 03:27.295
He was...
One at a time, all right?

03:27.297 --> 03:28.662
Did you see which way
the guy fled?

03:28.664 --> 03:29.663
Yes, he went that way.

03:29.665 --> 03:30.998
No, no, huh-huh, he goes

03:31.000 --> 03:32.633
this way, all right?
And he's a black guy.

03:32.635 --> 03:34.218
WOMAN: What do you know?
You were

03:34.220 --> 03:36.170
all the way over there
in your barfmobile.
Officer?

03:36.172 --> 03:37.638
Look, shut up, you rich bitch, okay?!
Oh, don't yell at me,

03:37.640 --> 03:39.056
falafel man.
BAEZ: Hey, now, okay...

03:39.058 --> 03:40.674
MAN: Look, she can't call me
these kind of things...!

03:40.676 --> 03:42.093
BAEZ: All right,
you, over there...

03:42.095 --> 03:44.061
Tell me you got
this thing on tape.

03:44.063 --> 03:46.981
No. I want a
picture with you.

03:46.983 --> 03:49.117
We're from Idaho.

03:49.119 --> 03:51.068
This is so cool!

03:51.070 --> 03:54.122
Yeah. Real cool.

